Again, I think if you told that story five years ago people would think you=
 were nuts. =E2=80=9CNo no no,=E2=80=9D they would say, =E2=80=9Cyou can=E2=
=80=99t manufacture safe dollar assets out of Bitcoin, Bitcoin is too volat=
ile, there is no floor, it could go to zero, this is nonsense.=E2=80=9D I t=
hink there is a good chance=C2=A0that if you tell that story five years fro=
m now it will be=C2=A0<em>unremarkable</em>. =E2=80=9CYes right of course t=
he Bank of Tether issues deposits worth one Tether and uses those deposits =
to fund margin loans to levered Bitcoin investors, that=E2=80=99s just how =
banking works,=E2=80=9D people will say. It is just a function of how confi=
dent people are in Bitcoin=E2=80=99s permanence and its function as a store=
 of value. Right now we are in between;=C2=A0the story is plausible but sti=
ll weird. It=E2=80=99s not the story that Tether wants to tell, and it=E2=
=80=99s not the main story of Tether. But it's the interesting part.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This has gone on long enough but I do want to end=
 on a couple of discussion questions:</p><ol type=3D"1" style=3D"list-style=
-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">Traditional financial regulators seem=C2=A0<em>very=C2=A0</e=
