ompany could have to liquidate its assets at a loss, setting off a run on t=
he not-bank. The losses could cascade into the regulated financial system b=
y crashing credit markets.=E2=80=9D) If you found out that, instead of bein=
g backed by U.S. Treasury bills and highly-rated commercial paper of large =
multinational companies, Tether is mostly backed by loans collateralized by=
 Bitcoins, how would that make you feel about the threat that Tether does o=
r does not pose to the traditional financial system?</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
