</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An important=C2=A0problem in finance i=
s:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16=
px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There are private companies.</l=
i>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You would like to buy their stock.</=
li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But they=E2=80=99re=C2=A0private, s=
o you can=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a=
 related problem, which is that some people are shareholders of private com=
panies=C2=A0(employees or venture capitalists) and would like to=C2=A0<em>s=
ell=C2=A0</em>their stock, but let us focus on the other problem because it=
 seems more popular. Some big famous tech startup is private, you keep hear=
ing about it, you use its products, you read that it raised money at a $40 =
billion valuation, you expect=C2=A0that it will eventually do an initial pu=
blic offering at an $80 billion valuation, you love it, but there is nothin=
